mapMarkers.title: Englischer Garten
mapMarkers.info: Very popular scenic park, more internaitonal than its name would suggest, it contains a Greek temple, Chinese pagoda and Japanese tea house.

mapMarkers.title: Eisbach Wave
mapMarkers.info: There's year-round surfing on this continuous wave on the Englischer Garten's Eisbach River,legalized in the summer of 2010 only for experienced.

mapMarkers.title: Marienplatz
mapMarkers.info: This prominent public square, the largest in Munich, still stands as the center of social activity in the city, much as it has throughout history.

mapMarkers.title: Peterskirche
mapMarkers.info: This 11th-century cathedral, the city's oldest remaining church, is best known for its beautiful golden interior.

mapMarkers.title: Hofbr√§uhaus
mapMarkers.info: This famous beer hall, founded in the late 16th century, is an extremely popular destination for tourists looking to experience local culture.

mapMarkers.title: Frauenkirche
mapMarkers.info: The Frauenkirche is a church in the Bavarian city of Munich that serves as the cathedral of the Archdiocese of Munich and Freising and seat of its Archbishop. It is a landmark and is considered a symbol of the Bavarian capital city.

mapMarkers.title: Olympiapark
mapMarkers.info: Olympiahalle is a multi-purpose arena located in Am Riesenfeld in Munich, Germany, part of Olympiapark.

mapMarkers.title: Viktualienmarkt
mapMarkers.info: The Viktualienmarkt is a daily food market and a square in the center of Munich, Germany. The Viktualienmarkt developed from an original farmers' market to a popular market for gourmets.
